intro: Cyanothamnus warangensis, commonly known as the Warangensis bluebottle, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Rutaceae and is characterized by its striking blue to violet flowers. The plant typically grows in coastal areas and is adapted to sandy soils. It has narrow, linear leaves and is often found in heathland environments. Cyanothamnus warangensis is valued for its ornamental appeal and ecological importance in supporting local wildlife.
